context: Having removed the monarchical government, Gaddafi proclaimed the foundation of the <a4_0>Libyan Arab Republic<a4_0/>. <a0_0>Addressing the populace by radio<a0_0/>, he proclaimed an end to the "<a8_0>reactionary and corrupt<a8_0/>" regime, "the stench of which has sickened and horrified us all." Due to the coup's bloodless nature, it was initially labelled the <a1_0>"<a5_0>White Revolution<a5_0/>", although was later renamed the "<a6_0>One September Revolution<a6_0/>"<a1_0/> after the date on which it occurred. Gaddafi insisted that the <a7_0>Free Officers<a7_0/>' coup represented <a3_0>a revolution<a3_0/>, marking the start of widespread change in the socio-economic and political nature of Libya. He proclaimed that the revolution meant "<a2_0>freedom, socialism, and unity<a2_0/>", and over the coming years implemented measures to achieve this.
